race.comment: Tricky. MISS GRAYSEA (8) turned the form around, leading and winning her Maiden at Coffs Harbour over this distance as a short price favourite. Expect that to stack up and she's a decent chance to go back-to-back. MISS ZERMATT (4) was heading in the right direction before being outgraded at the Gold Coast. She peaks in a more suitable assignment and maps for a soft run. MARATHIA (6) flopped on the Gold Coast poly up in trip and may have had excuses. She missed a nose prior in a Casino CL2 over 1200m, and that form would give her a chance. WANJINA ROSE (7) deserved her 50 win at Taree this journey. Has a wide gate, but the 3kg claim brings her into it.
